<br>
I note you used the word &quot;liberal&quot; as a semi-derrogatory adjective.  If you break that word down into it's basic word parts you would discover that it is based around the word &quot;Liberty&quot;.  <br>
<br>
You've become a victim of conservative talk radio if you think &quot;liberal&quot; can be used as a derrogatory term.<br>
<br>
Since when did the concept of invidual liberty become an acceptable mainstream target for any American?<br>
<br>
As for unreasonable search and seizure, what you describe as resonable to you is well beyond the constitutional definition of reasonable.  If there is not reason to suspect a crime is taking place, then there is no reason to condone a search.  A search warrant is required since no liberty can be removed without Due Process.  The reasonable suspicions are contained within the search warrant, and dictate exactly where and what to sea ch for.  Removing Due Process (in this case via the Patriot Act) is equivalent to abolishing constitutional rights. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=treeslover>Treeslover</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 1881<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/7/03 4:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Freedom</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>But do you want to live in one? Okay, maybe you do.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
